From 056e3c70b33abb1321256706807d96521e3770e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: athk enable sending TPC power command for MHz

TPE spec is not yet defined for 320 MHz. However, for proper
Tx power related calculations, it is mandatory to send SET_TPC_POWER
command to firmware in 320 MHz as well.

Add support to form and send the TPC power command for 320 MHz bandwidth
as well.

Signed-off-by: Aditya Kumar Singh <quic_adisi@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <quic_gauthamk@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 include/linux/ieee80211.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/include/linux/ieee80211.h b/include/linux/ieee80211.h
index 8ee8b6a..b6aba32 100644
--- a/include/linux/ieee80211.h
+++ b/include/linux/ieee80211.h
@@ -2839,6 +2839,7 @@ enum ieee80211_tx_power_category_6ghz {
 	IEEE80211_TPE_CAT_6GHZ_SUBORDINATE = 1,
 };
 
+#define IEEE80211_MAX_NUM_PWR_LEVEL    16
 /*
  * For IEEE80211_TPE_LOCAL_EIRP / IEEE80211_TPE_REG_CLIENT_EIRP,
  * setting to 63.5 dBm means no constraint.
-- 
2.34.1

